==Old English==
===Etymology===
From Germanic ''*strawam'' ‘that which is strewn’.  Cognate with Old Frisian [[stre|strē]], Old Saxon [[stro|strō]] (Dutch [[stroo]]), Old High German [[stro|strō]] (German [[Stroh]]), Old Norse [[strá]] (Swedish [[strå]]).

